llm_res.rule: transferFrom: Transfers _value amount of tokens from address _from to address _to, and MUST fire the Transfer event. The transferFrom method is used for a withdraw workflow, allowing contracts to transfer tokens on your behalf. This can be used for example to allow a contract to transfer tokens on your behalf and/or to charge fees in sub-currencies. The function SHOULD throw unless the _from account has deliberately authorized the sender of the message via some mechanism.
A mechanism is provided to associate NFTs with URIs.
